# üêû bug report


### Affected Package
This bug report is for @angular/core


### Is this a regression?

Yes


### Description

I have updated my project from angular 10.0.4 to 10.0.6.

In my app.module.ts file I register my locale and provides the LOCALE_ID and the DatePipe.

<pre><code>
import localeSv from '@angular/common/locales/sv';
registerLocaleData(localeSv);
...
providers: [ { provide: LOCALE_ID, useValue: 'sv' }, DatePipe ]
</code></pre>


This DatePipe is then injected into a pipe of my own that among other things does `this.datePipe.transform(startTime, 'fullDate');`

As of 10.0.6 the transform function throws an exception telling me it does not find the 'sv' locale data. This is only present in my production builds and the pipe works as expected with "ng serve" on localhost.

(No locale info in pipe Error: InvalidPipeArgument: 'Missing locale data for the locale "sv".' for pipe 't')

